10:
My Lady, we must retreat! It is not
safe here!
29:
It's good to be home! Especially
after today...
31:
What did you think of the Kingdom
of Sand, Nevia?
36:
To think there was a world with no
beastfolk—only humans... It was very
interesting.
38:
...Although from the state of their
world, it seems conflict is inevitable
no matter where you go.
42:
Hmph... You say that, but that
hellhole ain't exactly a good
reference point.
47:
Ah, sorry, guys, I gotta go! I have a
practice match after this!
52: That boy certainly is a strange one...
65:
Yeah... I got my butt kicked pretty
hard, so I'm just sitting here trying to
figure out how to not suck so much...
73: Do you always practice like this?
76:
Well, I'm a lot weaker than everyone
else, so—
79: You are a terrible liar, Alk.
82:
At Claw's request, I have observed
you throughout our adventures in
the Kaleidoscope and other worlds.
84:
You have witnessed the stream of
fate many times over, yet your
resolve never weakens...
87: You are, in fact, incredibly strong, Alk.
91:
I-I don't know about that... But I
guess what I should be saying is...
Thanks.
95: Are you unable to forgive yourself?
102:
Can you not stand the fact that you
are powerless? That... you too are
being carried along by a higher
power?
104:
Surely that must be the reason you
continue to fight.
111:
I don't know if I ever feel that angry
about it...
114:
Mainly, I just don't want to have any
regrets. I never want to feel like I
could or should have been able to
do more.
116:
So even if I do feel powerless or
whatever, I don't know if I'd be that
harsh on myself. I'd probably be too
busy worrying about other stuff.
121:
I see... Well, being strict with oneself
is different from anger.
136: Heh... Hehe. Ah, I see now...
139:
What I was feeling back then was
anger.
143:
Heh, that's not something you
expect to hear from a sage.
146:
If you're looking for someone who
feels the same as you, you're looking
in the wrong place. Alk's not the
raging type.
149:
So it seems. Perhaps I would do
better in your company?
153:
Huh? Wait, when did you two start
getting along so well?
157:
Alk, if you had told me you couldn't
forgive yourself, I would have
advised you to let go of those fears
and accept reality.
160:
But I now believe you have no need
of such advice.
163:
Because it was I who was unable to
let go... of my anger.
170:
Yes... And now that I think about it, 
I have been for a very long time.
Angry at the weak, the world, and
most of all—myself.
172: I feel so much rage towards it all.
176:
You certainly don't look it... I'd hate to
see how angry you'd have to be to
show it...
179:
Oh, it is a fearsome sight. I can
assure you of that.
182:
Well, now that I have come to terms
with my true feelings, I suppose 
I must rejoin Claw and offer my
support.
186:
But before that, I think it would befit
a sage such as myself to take a
page from Alk's book.
190:
Now that sounds interesting. 
Mind if I join you?
195: So wait... How exactly did I help here?
